#: ../../H/high-moby.rst:5
msgid "high moby"
msgstr "high moby"

#: ../../H/high-moby.rst:7
msgid "/hi:´ mohb´ee/, n\\."
msgstr "/hi:´ mohb´ee/, 名詞"

#: ../../H/high-moby.rst:9
msgid ""
"The high half of a 512K :ref:`PDP-10`\\'s physical address space; the other "
"half was of course the low moby. This usage has been generalized in a way "
"that has outlasted the :ref:`PDP-10`\\; for example, at the 1990 Washington "
"D.C. Area Science Fiction Conclave (Disclave), when a miscommunication "
"resulted in two separate wakes being held in commemoration of the shutdown "
"of MIT's last :ref:`ITS` machines, the one on the upper floor was dubbed the"
" ‘high moby’ and the other the ‘low moby’. All parties involved "
":ref:`grok`\\ked this instantly. See :ref:`moby`\\."
msgstr ""
"512Kの\\ :ref:`PDP-10`\\ の物理アドレス空間の上半分。もう半分はもちろんlow mobyだった。この用法は\\ "
":ref:`PDP-10`\\ "
"より長く生き延びる仕方で一般化された。例えば、1990年のワシントンD.C.地区SFコンクレーブ(Disclave)で、伝達ミスによってMITの最後の\\"
" :ref:`ITS`\\ マシンの停止を記念して2つの別々の通夜が開かれたとき、上階のものは‘high moby’、もう一方は‘low "
"moby’と名付けられた。関係者全員がこれを即座に\\ :ref:`grok`\\ した。\\ :ref:`moby`\\ を参照。"
